WEBVTT


00:00:18.940 --> 00:00:23.880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:29.260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:37.010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

00:00:38.210 --> 00:00:43.120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

00:00:44.650 --> 00:00:47.930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

00:00:47.930 --> 00:00:51.000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

00:00:51.710 --> 00:00:56.660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

00:00:57.700 --> 00:01:00.880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:04.160
♪The open sky rises high♪

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:09.830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:13.860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

00:01:13.860 --> 00:01:17.220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

00:01:17.630 --> 00:01:23.300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

00:01:23.710 --> 00:01:26.960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:30.290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:34.730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

00:01:34.730 --> 00:01:35.980
=The Lead=

00:01:36.020 --> 00:01:37.900
=Episode 29=

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:42.500
(Diaojia Village)

00:01:42.510 --> 00:01:43.360
Over here. Right here.

00:01:44.800 --> 00:01:46.510
Look, this is the spot.

00:01:47.190 --> 00:01:48.030
What do you think?

00:01:49.270 --> 00:01:50.270
This whole side is good

00:01:50.270 --> 00:01:51.560
for your stools and stuff.

00:01:51.640 --> 00:01:53.510
It's by the village entrance.
Great spot.

00:01:53.830 --> 00:01:56.030
I went to Laohei at dawn

00:01:56.030 --> 00:01:57.550
and finally got him to find us a place.

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:00.490
I've cleared it

00:02:00.490 --> 00:02:01.920
with the family here.

00:02:02.030 --> 00:02:03.160
There's a well in the back.

00:02:03.160 --> 00:02:04.510
Use all the water you need.

00:02:04.550 --> 00:02:05.510
They're really nice.

00:02:06.120 --> 00:02:07.640
Great. Let's set up the stall.

00:02:08.350 --> 00:02:09.190
Okay.

00:02:34.560 --> 00:02:35.560
All right, all right.

00:02:35.560 --> 00:02:36.640
Stop. No more practice.

00:02:37.240 --> 00:02:38.519
Let Director Gu finish coughing.

00:02:48.133 --> 00:02:49.150
Director Gu, are you okay?

00:02:49.150 --> 00:02:49.990
I'm fine.

00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:53.350
I was too worried to sleep last night.

00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:54.960
What's up?

00:02:55.560 --> 00:02:58.760
About this national
local opera showcase,

00:02:59.560 --> 00:03:00.510
why did the authorities

00:03:00.510 --> 00:03:03.280
pick You Xi Hu?

00:03:05.510 --> 00:03:06.760
Don't beat around the bush.

00:03:08.120 --> 00:03:08.960
Look.

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:11.510
We should show the leaders

00:03:12.120 --> 00:03:14.710
what they want to see, right?

00:03:14.950 --> 00:03:17.710
We also need to make them happy.

00:03:19.350 --> 00:03:22.120
We've rehearsed Sha Sheng three times

00:03:22.710 --> 00:03:24.840
without fire breathing.

00:03:25.350 --> 00:03:27.070
Here's what I'm worried about:

00:03:27.430 --> 00:03:28.920
If a part slips and causes trouble

00:03:29.310 --> 00:03:32.120
during the three-part coordination,

00:03:32.760 --> 00:03:35.230
we'll be done.

00:03:37.640 --> 00:03:38.950
That's exactly right.

00:03:38.950 --> 00:03:39.790
Right?

00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:41.150
That's what I thought too.

00:03:41.150 --> 00:03:41.990
Yeah.

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:44.240
Lili,

00:03:44.840 --> 00:03:46.360
how's your fire breathing going?

00:03:46.470 --> 00:03:47.320
I'm at it.

00:03:47.320 --> 00:03:48.310
I've been at it nonstop.

00:03:48.400 --> 00:03:49.280
Good.

00:03:49.280 --> 00:03:50.960
Do it with fire breathing.

00:03:51.240 --> 00:03:52.080
Now?

00:03:53.016 --> 00:03:54.150
Why didn't you say so sooner?

00:03:54.150 --> 00:03:55.520
I didn't bring Baozi today.

00:03:55.870 --> 00:03:56.710
I can't do it.

00:03:58.030 --> 00:03:59.150
No Baozi with her.

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:01.840
Then...

00:04:03.310 --> 00:04:05.710
Let's see who has one today.

00:04:07.360 --> 00:04:09.360
Who brought Baozi?

00:04:09.910 --> 00:04:11.470
Which one of you brought Baozi?

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:12.910
Anyone got Baozi?

00:04:12.910 --> 00:04:14.750
- Raise your hand. Let me see.
- No.

00:04:14.750 --> 00:04:16.190
Who brought Baozi?

00:04:17.310 --> 00:04:18.190
Who brought it?

00:04:22.520 --> 00:04:23.360
You did?

00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:25.680
Let Gong Lili use Baozi.

00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:27.470
Why would she bring it? Can she use it?

00:04:27.470 --> 00:04:28.310
No idea.

00:04:34.310 --> 00:04:35.430
Don't come any closer.

00:04:35.840 --> 00:04:36.910
It's your Baozi.

00:04:37.080 --> 00:04:38.120
How can I use it?

00:04:38.840 --> 00:04:39.680
I can't do it.

00:04:43.240 --> 00:04:44.840
Shall we let Yi Qin'e try?

00:04:46.680 --> 00:04:47.710
You decide.

00:04:50.280 --> 00:04:51.710
Why are you looking at me?

00:04:52.310 --> 00:04:53.910
You carried it with you.

00:04:54.190 --> 00:04:55.176
You've practiced, right?

00:04:55.710 --> 00:04:56.840
Come on, give it a try.

00:04:57.030 --> 00:04:58.030
Come on, get ready.

00:04:58.030 --> 00:04:58.910
Light it.

00:05:09.960 --> 00:05:10.800
Great.

00:05:13.910 --> 00:05:16.310
Bravo.

00:05:17.320 --> 00:05:18.160
Great.

00:05:18.240 --> 00:05:19.080
Bravo.

00:05:19.590 --> 00:05:20.430
Awesome.

00:05:22.020 --> 00:05:22.880
Great.

00:05:22.910 --> 00:05:23.750
Director Gu,

00:05:24.680 --> 00:05:25.870
there's still a meeting.

00:05:26.030 --> 00:05:27.080
I'll head over first.

00:05:27.520 --> 00:05:29.080
Go on, go.

00:05:30.280 --> 00:05:31.470
How's your cough?

00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:33.840
Is your cough better?

00:05:37.520 --> 00:05:38.470
Much better.

00:05:41.080 --> 00:05:42.310
Much better now.

00:05:43.310 --> 00:05:44.150
Good.

00:05:44.680 --> 00:05:46.280
That's it for rehearsal today.

00:05:52.710 --> 00:05:53.560
You're really good.

00:05:53.560 --> 00:05:54.800
So impressive.

00:05:55.080 --> 00:05:55.920
That's amazing.

00:05:55.920 --> 00:05:56.800
When did you practice?

00:05:56.800 --> 00:05:58.720
- Well done.
- What a surprise.

00:05:58.720 --> 00:06:00.040
- Teach us.
- Can you teach us?

00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:01.720
Alright, alright. Let's wrap it up.

00:06:02.310 --> 00:06:03.560
Put the carpet back.

00:06:03.560 --> 00:06:04.400
Bye.

00:06:10.830 --> 00:06:11.680
See that?

00:06:12.270 --> 00:06:13.390
Things as easy as that

00:06:13.920 --> 00:06:15.720
have already stunned them.

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:18.390
Wait for my good news.

00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:29.430
I don't know how you crawled
to the provincial capital,

00:06:29.800 --> 00:06:32.070
but with your tacky vocal style

00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:34.240
and on cheap charm,

00:06:34.390 --> 00:06:36.040
you won't be able to squeeze

00:06:36.310 --> 00:06:37.480
onto Chang'an's stage.

00:06:56.360 --> 00:06:57.680
So tasty.

00:06:58.210 --> 00:06:59.070
Mix him another bowl.

00:06:59.070 --> 00:06:59.930
Sure.

00:06:59.950 --> 00:07:01.680
Enough, I've had a few bowls.

00:07:01.680 --> 00:07:02.870
- I'll mix it.
- Enjoy.

00:07:02.870 --> 00:07:03.800
If you get hungry later,

00:07:03.800 --> 00:07:04.750
come by my place.

00:07:04.750 --> 00:07:06.160
It's on the house.

00:07:07.720 --> 00:07:08.680
I can't let you do that.

00:07:08.870 --> 00:07:10.120
Go ask around.

00:07:10.240 --> 00:07:11.560
Here in Diaojia Village,

00:07:11.680 --> 00:07:13.070
I always pay for the food,

00:07:13.070 --> 00:07:14.160
drinks,

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:15.160
and groceries.

00:07:15.830 --> 00:07:17.310
I don't take things

00:07:17.310 --> 00:07:18.750
for free.

00:07:18.970 --> 00:07:19.830
That's loyalty.

00:07:19.830 --> 00:07:20.950
- Laohei.
- Yeah.

00:07:20.950 --> 00:07:22.360
Where to? Have you eaten?

00:07:22.750 --> 00:07:24.160
We were going for noodles.

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:25.360
Noodles? What noodles?

00:07:25.360 --> 00:07:26.560
Come sit. Have liangpi here.

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:28.270
We want noodles.

00:07:28.270 --> 00:07:30.070
What? Listen to me.

00:07:30.430 --> 00:07:32.190
Real Ningzhou liangpi is amazing.

00:07:32.190 --> 00:07:33.430
Sit there. Eat.

00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:36.190
Ma'am, two bowls each first.

00:07:36.190 --> 00:07:37.160
- Sure.
- Eight bowls.

00:07:37.160 --> 00:07:38.000
- Okay.
- Eat.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.120
Laohei wants to treat today, right?

00:07:40.190 --> 00:07:42.000
Treat? Pay on your own.

00:07:42.510 --> 00:07:43.480
Both vinegar and chili?

00:07:43.830 --> 00:07:44.750
Yeah.

00:07:44.750 --> 00:07:45.590
Laohei.

00:07:46.630 --> 00:07:47.480
Have you eaten?

00:07:47.480 --> 00:07:48.330
- Not yet.
- Not yet.

00:07:48.330 --> 00:07:49.630
Perfect. Sit down for liangpi.

00:07:49.800 --> 00:07:50.830
Liangpi?

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:52.240
- Sit and eat.
- Okay.

00:07:52.240 --> 00:07:54.000
Ma'am, two bowls each for them.

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:54.840
Sure.

00:07:55.920 --> 00:07:56.760
We're all brothers.

00:07:59.480 --> 00:08:01.480
Ma'am, if anything comes up,

00:08:01.480 --> 00:08:02.870
just come to me.

00:08:02.870 --> 00:08:03.816
I can handle everything.

00:08:03.830 --> 00:08:05.070
Thanks, Laohei.

00:08:05.430 --> 00:08:06.270
No need to thank me.

00:08:07.870 --> 00:08:11.920
I look up at the endless sky.

00:08:12.120 --> 00:08:13.480
Why is this world...

00:08:13.480 --> 00:08:15.040
This script we're using now

00:08:15.040 --> 00:08:18.040
is the 1953 revised version.

00:08:18.040 --> 00:08:21.480
I've cut and changed some parts.

00:08:22.070 --> 00:08:23.560
That's based

00:08:23.560 --> 00:08:25.480
on the real issues we've hit

00:08:25.480 --> 00:08:27.240
in the past half-month of rehearsals.

00:08:27.830 --> 00:08:29.600
Share your thoughts, everyone.

00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:30.560
Hold on.

00:08:35.430 --> 00:08:36.360
You cut lines?

00:08:36.700 --> 00:08:37.600
Right.

00:08:37.600 --> 00:08:38.680
Like I just said,

00:08:38.680 --> 00:08:40.800
I've made some tweaks.

00:08:41.430 --> 00:08:42.870
For Li Hui Niang,

00:08:42.870 --> 00:08:43.870
here's what I think.

00:08:43.870 --> 00:08:45.830
Once she drops into the Woyu posture,

00:08:46.270 --> 00:08:48.430
the follow spot comes in and tightens;

00:08:48.480 --> 00:08:50.390
then the fade-out ends the scene.

00:08:50.390 --> 00:08:52.270
A deliberate blank space has more charm.

00:08:52.270 --> 00:08:54.270
The following sung lines are too plain.

00:08:54.270 --> 00:08:55.870
It feels tacked on. No point.

00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:57.110
Director Feng,

00:08:57.830 --> 00:09:00.270
our A role for Li Hui Niang

00:09:00.430 --> 00:09:02.390
is best at singing.

00:09:03.270 --> 00:09:05.270
If you cut so many sung lines,

00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:08.800
the skill work becomes the top priority.

00:09:09.190 --> 00:09:10.800
But you know

00:09:10.800 --> 00:09:11.870
her Woyu posture.

00:09:12.380 --> 00:09:14.860
Isn't that like building a fire pit

00:09:14.940 --> 00:09:16.380
and putting her on it to roast?

00:09:16.780 --> 00:09:18.380
Right, that's what I was about to say.

00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:21.180
Yi Qin'e's fire breathing

00:09:21.180 --> 00:09:23.300
really shocked me.

00:09:23.300 --> 00:09:24.780
I think it's great.

00:09:25.180 --> 00:09:27.140
I realized something serious:

00:09:27.460 --> 00:09:28.780
A lot of skills

00:09:28.780 --> 00:09:31.100
like Woyu and fire breathing

00:09:31.540 --> 00:09:35.340
aren't really secret techniques.

00:09:35.540 --> 00:09:36.980
Most are open to the audience

00:09:37.060 --> 00:09:38.780
and to fellow artists.

00:09:38.780 --> 00:09:41.580
Why can only a few actresses

00:09:41.580 --> 00:09:43.100
actually pull it off?

00:09:43.100 --> 00:09:44.540
The answer is actually simple.

00:09:44.860 --> 00:09:47.220
It's just way too hard.

00:09:47.220 --> 00:09:49.740
Not everyone can master this skill.

00:09:49.740 --> 00:09:51.540
One word matters most here.

00:09:51.540 --> 00:09:52.700
Talent.

00:09:53.060 --> 00:09:54.580
Of course.

00:09:54.580 --> 00:09:56.100
You've got to have talent.

00:09:56.100 --> 00:09:57.340
Isn't that obvious?

00:09:57.780 --> 00:10:00.380
So, Troupe Leader, I have a new idea.

00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:03.140
Since Yi Qin'e has that talent,

00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:04.940
let her take the stage.

00:10:06.340 --> 00:10:07.260
And then?

00:10:08.460 --> 00:10:10.380
As for Yi Qin'e's issue,

00:10:10.380 --> 00:10:14.460
her vocal style is too rustic.

00:10:16.100 --> 00:10:17.860
That won't change in a day or two.

00:10:17.860 --> 00:10:19.380
So, for the sung lines,

00:10:19.380 --> 00:10:21.180
I think Gong Lili should still do them.

00:10:22.580 --> 00:10:24.100
So, you mean...

00:10:25.140 --> 00:10:26.180
A double.

00:10:26.580 --> 00:10:27.740
Have Yi Qin'e

00:10:27.740 --> 00:10:30.780
double Gong Lili's Woyu
and fire breathing.

00:10:33.580 --> 00:10:34.420
How would that work?

00:10:34.940 --> 00:10:37.700
You'd have two Li Hui Niangs
in one scene?

00:10:38.340 --> 00:10:40.580
That was impossible before.

00:10:40.580 --> 00:10:41.860
But on today's stage,

00:10:41.860 --> 00:10:43.580
all of that is possible now.

00:10:43.580 --> 00:10:45.340
With lighting, sound,
and effects aligned,

00:10:45.340 --> 00:10:46.180
they'll be both

00:10:46.190 --> 00:10:48.780
vivid Li Hui Niangs on stage.

00:10:48.980 --> 00:10:50.580
Once the audience is drawn in,

00:10:50.580 --> 00:10:51.980
I think it'll work just fine.

00:10:51.980 --> 00:10:52.860
They won't mind.

00:10:52.870 --> 00:10:53.730
Nonsense.

00:10:56.660 --> 00:10:58.180
This is total nonsense.

00:10:58.780 --> 00:11:00.380
The lead is the lead for a reason.

00:11:00.380 --> 00:11:01.240
Director Gu,

00:11:01.300 --> 00:11:03.940
the era of the lead
carrying a whole show

00:11:03.940 --> 00:11:05.380
is over.

00:11:05.380 --> 00:11:08.500
My idea can push their strengths

00:11:08.500 --> 00:11:09.380
to the fullest.

00:11:09.380 --> 00:11:10.900
What kind of idea is that?

00:11:10.900 --> 00:11:12.380
Okay, okay, Director Gu.

00:11:13.380 --> 00:11:14.220
Director Gu,

00:11:15.180 --> 00:11:16.980
I think Director Feng has a point.

00:11:17.100 --> 00:11:18.780
Everyone has their strengths, right?

00:11:18.780 --> 00:11:19.620
What strengths?

00:11:19.780 --> 00:11:20.660
Clarify that.

00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:21.940
How would I know?

00:11:21.940 --> 00:11:23.460
- You...
- Come on.

00:11:23.460 --> 00:11:24.900
This makes no sense.

00:11:24.900 --> 00:11:26.140
Let's talk it through.

00:11:26.140 --> 00:11:26.980
Why are you yelling?

00:11:29.020 --> 00:11:29.860
Well...

00:11:31.420 --> 00:11:33.300
Innovation can be interesting.

00:11:34.620 --> 00:11:37.780
Keeping tradition has value too.

00:11:38.020 --> 00:11:38.900
Exactly.

00:11:39.420 --> 00:11:43.620
But Director Feng's artistic blend

00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:44.900
isn't impossible either.

00:11:45.220 --> 00:11:46.060
Think about it.

00:11:46.540 --> 00:11:48.940
One role, two actresses.

00:11:49.100 --> 00:11:51.020
That way, no one has to fight over it.

00:11:51.420 --> 00:11:52.620
They can both do it.

00:11:52.820 --> 00:11:54.220
It'll help with the scenes too.

00:11:54.700 --> 00:11:55.540
What do you think?

00:12:00.660 --> 00:12:02.100
Then go tell the actresses.

00:12:03.860 --> 00:12:05.100
Let me make this clear.

00:12:05.620 --> 00:12:07.300
If an actress agrees to this,

00:12:07.580 --> 00:12:08.940
all her role prep

00:12:09.380 --> 00:12:10.820
will be wasted.

00:12:22.900 --> 00:12:23.860
Which one of you

00:12:24.900 --> 00:12:27.700
is going to tell the actresses?

00:12:43.140 --> 00:12:44.100
What are you staring at?

00:12:45.420 --> 00:12:46.580
Go keep an eye on them.

00:12:46.940 --> 00:12:47.980
See what they're planning.

00:12:48.820 --> 00:12:49.660
Hurry up.

00:13:01.820 --> 00:13:02.940
Master!

00:13:03.140 --> 00:13:04.220
Troupe Leader Shan is out.

00:13:06.060 --> 00:13:06.900
Quick!

00:13:09.140 --> 00:13:09.980
Troupe Leader Shan.

00:13:22.380 --> 00:13:26.580
(Rehearsal Hall)

00:13:28.380 --> 00:13:29.700
Go keep an eye on her.

00:13:29.880 --> 00:13:30.740
Who?

00:13:30.780 --> 00:13:31.980
On Yi Qin'e, of course.

00:13:32.300 --> 00:13:34.220
That guy must be talking to Yi Qin'e.

00:13:34.380 --> 00:13:35.220
Watch closely.

00:13:35.340 --> 00:13:36.420
If she's about to say yes,

00:13:36.420 --> 00:13:37.380
stop her right away.

00:13:37.420 --> 00:13:38.540
You have to stop her.

00:13:38.940 --> 00:13:39.810
Go.

00:13:45.380 --> 00:13:46.420
Comrade Yi Qin'e.

00:13:47.300 --> 00:13:48.140
Troupe Leader.

00:13:49.460 --> 00:13:52.060
Come here. I need to tell you something.

00:13:52.660 --> 00:13:53.660
What is it?

00:13:53.940 --> 00:13:54.800
Sit,

00:13:54.860 --> 00:13:55.700
and let's talk.

00:13:59.860 --> 00:14:02.220
Here's what we're thinking.

00:14:30.180 --> 00:14:31.020
Master.

00:14:31.780 --> 00:14:32.900
You scared me.

00:14:33.820 --> 00:14:34.700
Why did you come out?

00:14:34.946 --> 00:14:36.180
Troupe Leader Shan and Yi Qin'e

00:14:36.180 --> 00:14:37.500
have talked there for a while.

00:14:37.580 --> 00:14:38.493
What were they saying?

00:14:38.780 --> 00:14:39.753
I couldn't hear clearly.

00:14:40.180 --> 00:14:41.660
Then why did you go in?

00:14:41.980 --> 00:14:43.140
Can't I watch from here?

00:14:45.580 --> 00:14:46.420
Where are they?

00:14:47.260 --> 00:14:48.140
Gu Cunxiao.

00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:50.340
What are you doing?

00:14:56.820 --> 00:14:57.660
What is it?

00:14:58.660 --> 00:14:59.860
Come here. Come here.

00:15:00.140 --> 00:15:01.540
Talking to me won't help.

00:15:01.900 --> 00:15:04.100
If the actress refuses, I can't help it.

00:15:05.860 --> 00:15:08.220
That girl is truly a good kid.

00:15:08.360 --> 00:15:09.940
She sees the bigger picture.

00:15:12.380 --> 00:15:13.220
What do you mean?

00:15:13.500 --> 00:15:14.420
What did she say?

00:15:14.900 --> 00:15:16.020
The girl said

00:15:16.340 --> 00:15:19.620
she'll follow whatever is arranged.

00:15:20.980 --> 00:15:22.100
What a good kid.

00:15:22.500 --> 00:15:23.980
Master Gu, you're a good teacher too.

00:15:25.460 --> 00:15:26.300
Thanks a lot.

00:15:27.300 --> 00:15:30.260
You should learn from Qin'e.

00:15:31.300 --> 00:15:32.580
Always smiling.

00:15:32.580 --> 00:15:34.100
That's not a good thing.

00:15:36.300 --> 00:15:37.900
Thanks, Gu.

00:15:38.230 --> 00:15:39.120
No problem.

00:15:39.620 --> 00:15:49.260
♪From Hancheng County, Shaanxi♪

00:15:55.260 --> 00:16:02.420
♪A home in Xinghua Village♪

00:16:02.420 --> 00:16:08.940
♪A sibling match took a turn♪

00:16:09.340 --> 00:16:19.020
♪Blood in the hall proved the wrong♪

00:16:21.980 --> 00:16:22.820
Stop.

00:16:23.660 --> 00:16:25.260
Stop, stop.

00:16:26.660 --> 00:16:27.500
What's wrong?

00:16:29.820 --> 00:16:31.060
What are you singing?

00:16:31.260 --> 00:16:32.660
Opera. Why?

00:16:32.740 --> 00:16:33.580
Opera?

00:16:38.020 --> 00:16:39.580
You call that opera?

00:16:40.540 --> 00:16:41.540
This is an expert.

00:16:41.990 --> 00:16:42.930
You tell me.

00:16:42.940 --> 00:16:44.020
Show us how to sing.

00:16:44.020 --> 00:16:45.180
Fine, I'll do it.

00:16:45.180 --> 00:16:46.220
Mei Hou Wang.

00:16:46.220 --> 00:16:47.060
Show us.

00:16:47.060 --> 00:16:48.260
Move, move. Come on.

00:17:03.980 --> 00:17:04.820
Sing.

00:17:05.300 --> 00:17:06.500
What's the rush?

00:17:06.500 --> 00:17:07.740
I haven't even started.

00:17:15.660 --> 00:17:18.860
♪You carry the load♪

00:17:18.860 --> 00:17:20.060
Stop, stop.

00:17:20.500 --> 00:17:21.580
Come on, get out.

00:17:21.580 --> 00:17:24.020
You clown, what are you doing?

00:17:24.020 --> 00:17:25.260
Trying to fool us?

00:17:25.260 --> 00:17:27.300
I'm just kidding with you.

00:17:27.300 --> 00:17:29.780
Come on, follow along.

00:17:34.700 --> 00:17:35.540
One.

00:17:36.340 --> 00:17:37.780
First, no bragging.

00:17:38.460 --> 00:17:39.900
Second, no showing off.

00:17:39.900 --> 00:17:43.060
My family held office
for three generations.

00:17:43.060 --> 00:17:46.140
My grandpa met the Emperor.

00:17:46.140 --> 00:17:49.460
My grandma dined with the Empress.

00:17:49.460 --> 00:17:52.420
My dad wore an imperial yellow jacket.

00:17:52.420 --> 00:17:55.380
My mom wore fine silk and satin.

00:17:55.380 --> 00:17:59.220
We don't walk out.
We ride in sedan chairs.

00:17:59.220 --> 00:18:02.060
And back home, maids rub our backs.

00:18:02.060 --> 00:18:04.820
I eat from a jade bowl.

00:18:05.210 --> 00:18:07.560
Even our chamber pot has blue trim.

00:18:07.740 --> 00:18:09.540
(Yong Yue)
Stumbling, stumbling.

00:18:09.940 --> 00:18:10.780
Stumbling.

00:18:10.980 --> 00:18:12.580
Young man, where are you off to?

00:18:12.580 --> 00:18:14.140
I'm not serving you anymore.

00:18:14.430 --> 00:18:16.360
I'm going back to serve the expert.

00:18:23.980 --> 00:18:24.820
Tell me.

00:18:27.580 --> 00:18:29.100
Why did you agree to him?

00:18:31.300 --> 00:18:32.180
They want a double

00:18:33.020 --> 00:18:34.100
for opera.

00:18:35.500 --> 00:18:36.860
How shameless.

00:18:37.700 --> 00:18:39.900
No one has done opera like that.

00:18:40.660 --> 00:18:42.060
If we do it this way,

00:18:42.460 --> 00:18:43.380
we may make it, right?

00:18:43.580 --> 00:18:44.420
What?

00:18:44.900 --> 00:18:45.740
What do you want?

00:18:46.980 --> 00:18:48.580
Trying to remake the world?

00:18:48.820 --> 00:18:50.260
What are you thinking?

00:18:54.220 --> 00:18:55.580
Who taught you to say that?

00:18:57.460 --> 00:18:58.420
Lame Shan.

00:19:00.140 --> 00:19:01.700
Lame Shan...

00:19:05.020 --> 00:19:06.980
He preys on the old and fools kids.

00:19:07.140 --> 00:19:08.860
Can't you see that it's a lie?

00:19:09.060 --> 00:19:10.260
He makes you suffer

00:19:10.260 --> 00:19:11.740
and lets his actress shine.

00:19:11.740 --> 00:19:12.740
Don't you get it?

00:19:14.940 --> 00:19:15.900
I think

00:19:16.380 --> 00:19:17.860
that if I do the fire breathing,

00:19:18.340 --> 00:19:19.980
the applause will be for me.

00:19:20.660 --> 00:19:21.500
Once I hear it,

00:19:21.500 --> 00:19:22.660
it'll be mine.

00:19:23.660 --> 00:19:25.380
How is that helping others shine?

00:19:27.740 --> 00:19:29.140
I've seen foolish kids,

00:19:29.580 --> 00:19:31.540
but no one is as foolish as you.

00:19:31.900 --> 00:19:32.980
I'm not foolish.

00:19:33.060 --> 00:19:34.180
Do you know what the lead

00:19:34.580 --> 00:19:35.540
means?

00:19:36.420 --> 00:19:38.700
Do you still want to be the lead?

00:19:40.780 --> 00:19:41.620
Talk.

00:19:43.140 --> 00:19:45.100
I never wanted to be the lead.

00:19:46.140 --> 00:19:46.980
What?

00:19:49.820 --> 00:19:50.660
You...

00:19:53.460 --> 00:19:56.420
Say that to Master Gou.

00:20:17.940 --> 00:20:19.100
Eight Rules.

00:20:20.180 --> 00:20:22.740
First, no coming here.

00:20:22.940 --> 00:20:25.820
Second, no buying anything.

00:20:27.620 --> 00:20:30.820
No more buying food.

00:20:32.180 --> 00:20:34.660
No tossing money around here.

00:20:35.100 --> 00:20:36.700
I broke every rule.

00:20:44.380 --> 00:20:46.820
How is she so adorable?

00:20:48.060 --> 00:20:49.740
Are you blind or illiterate?

00:20:51.820 --> 00:20:52.860
I'll get you Jinggao.

00:20:53.180 --> 00:20:54.020
Jinggao.

00:20:58.540 --> 00:21:00.980
You have to eat.

00:21:01.340 --> 00:21:04.700
Jinggao tastes sweet and fragrant.

00:21:05.300 --> 00:21:06.180
Eat it while it's hot.

00:21:07.300 --> 00:21:09.660
You even made up Eight Rules.

00:21:09.660 --> 00:21:11.980
Now, I'm all thrown off.

00:21:12.780 --> 00:21:16.140
You can't stop me caring, right?

00:21:16.260 --> 00:21:18.540
Look here.

00:21:19.460 --> 00:21:21.980
Guangzhou denim wear.

00:21:23.180 --> 00:21:27.260
Stars wear this now.

00:21:27.740 --> 00:21:29.060
Try it on.

00:21:30.850 --> 00:21:32.310
- Just try it.
- I don't want to.

00:21:35.340 --> 00:21:37.140
How do you know if you don't try?

00:21:37.260 --> 00:21:38.100
Right?

00:21:38.460 --> 00:21:40.260
Come on. Once you put it on,

00:21:41.140 --> 00:21:46.540
you'll be the prettiest girl
in the troupe.

00:21:47.160 --> 00:21:48.020
Try it on.

00:21:48.380 --> 00:21:49.300
Feeling shy, huh?

00:21:49.900 --> 00:21:50.740
Got it.

00:21:51.840 --> 00:21:53.500
I'll pull the curtain.

00:21:54.620 --> 00:21:55.820
Take your time trying it on.

00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:58.100
Once you put it on,

00:21:58.420 --> 00:22:01.060
you'll feel full of life,

00:22:01.060 --> 00:22:03.060
facing the sun.

00:22:03.380 --> 00:22:06.300
You'll be lively.

00:22:06.460 --> 00:22:07.340
How lovely...

00:22:09.300 --> 00:22:11.060
Why kick so hard?

00:22:13.060 --> 00:22:14.700
As the saying goes,

00:22:14.860 --> 00:22:17.300
being scolded means they care.

00:22:17.500 --> 00:22:21.020
If you care, you'll kick me.

00:22:37.090 --> 00:22:38.130
Why are you crying?

00:22:39.130 --> 00:22:40.296
I was just messing with you.

00:22:42.140 --> 00:22:43.180
Our Eight Rules

00:22:43.180 --> 00:22:45.940
don't say I can't joke around, right?

00:22:47.220 --> 00:22:48.060
Okay.

00:22:48.060 --> 00:22:49.700
I was wrong, okay?

00:22:49.700 --> 00:22:50.900
I won't dare do it again.

00:22:50.900 --> 00:22:52.580
I won't tease you again, okay?

00:22:52.580 --> 00:22:53.540
Don't cry.

00:22:53.540 --> 00:22:55.700
Seeing you cry hurts me.

00:22:59.740 --> 00:23:01.060
Did someone pick on you?

00:23:01.060 --> 00:23:01.900
You.

00:23:02.340 --> 00:23:03.260
It was you.

00:23:03.380 --> 00:23:04.220
Get out.

00:23:04.380 --> 00:23:05.220
Okay, okay.

00:23:05.460 --> 00:23:06.900
I'll leave.

00:23:06.900 --> 00:23:08.500
I can leave.

00:23:09.620 --> 00:23:11.860
But if anyone messes with you,

00:23:12.140 --> 00:23:13.140
just tell me.

00:23:13.940 --> 00:23:15.500
I'll make them pay.

00:23:15.580 --> 00:23:16.420
It's me.

00:23:18.860 --> 00:23:19.700
Master Gu.

00:23:21.020 --> 00:23:22.413
It's my fault that she was wronged.

00:23:22.900 --> 00:23:24.700
Come on, kill me.

00:23:25.260 --> 00:23:26.100
Come on, do it.

00:23:26.100 --> 00:23:27.180
That's not what I meant.

00:23:27.330 --> 00:23:28.180
What's going on?

00:23:28.180 --> 00:23:29.020
Get out.

00:23:30.460 --> 00:23:31.740
Get the hell out.

00:23:32.980 --> 00:23:33.900
Stop making it worse.

00:23:34.550 --> 00:23:35.860
She can't even perform now.

00:23:37.820 --> 00:23:39.180
What play was it?

00:23:39.180 --> 00:23:40.060
Why so upset?

00:23:40.060 --> 00:23:40.900
What play?

00:23:40.910 --> 00:23:41.810
Da Jiao Zan.

00:23:41.830 --> 00:23:42.750
What play?

00:23:52.420 --> 00:23:53.260
Qin'e.

00:23:53.700 --> 00:23:54.980
Back in Ningzhou,

00:23:54.980 --> 00:23:56.140
I didn't have to worry.

00:23:57.300 --> 00:23:58.860
I just listened to the masters.

00:24:01.260 --> 00:24:02.580
Now, they're all gone.

00:24:02.620 --> 00:24:03.780
So, I listen to you.

00:24:05.740 --> 00:24:07.260
But now, I'm realizing

00:24:07.260 --> 00:24:08.140
that you also don't...

00:24:10.060 --> 00:24:11.620
You don't know what to do.

00:24:14.020 --> 00:24:15.460
I've got one thought now:

00:24:16.140 --> 00:24:17.420
Just follow my master's lead

00:24:18.100 --> 00:24:19.460
and finish the 81 bursts of fire.

00:24:19.980 --> 00:24:21.580
I can't handle the rest.

00:24:28.860 --> 00:24:30.060
What's up with you?

00:24:30.060 --> 00:24:31.460
You've had a few bathroom trips.

00:24:31.460 --> 00:24:32.340
My stomach hurts.

00:24:33.220 --> 00:24:35.940
Can I get two hawthorn pills to chew?

00:24:37.780 --> 00:24:40.100
I think you just ate too much liangpi.

00:24:40.940 --> 00:24:42.980
You can't eat that much
at this time of the year.

00:24:43.940 --> 00:24:45.140
Five meals a day.

00:24:46.340 --> 00:24:48.100
Eighteen bowls in total.

00:24:48.710 --> 00:24:51.060
Wu Song only had 18 bowls
before Jingyanggang.

00:24:52.820 --> 00:24:53.660
Sanyuan!

00:24:55.700 --> 00:24:56.540
Here.

00:24:56.740 --> 00:24:57.700
Liangpi.

00:24:57.940 --> 00:24:59.500
Ms. Hua asked me to bring it.

00:24:59.860 --> 00:25:00.740
Why?

00:25:00.740 --> 00:25:02.340
I was going to eat at the stall.

00:25:02.500 --> 00:25:03.340
Don't go.

00:25:03.660 --> 00:25:04.980
You'll just waste a trip.

00:25:05.050 --> 00:25:05.910
How come?

00:25:05.980 --> 00:25:07.660
Business was crazy today.

00:25:07.700 --> 00:25:08.580
All sold out early,

00:25:08.780 --> 00:25:09.700
so she closed up.

00:25:10.780 --> 00:25:12.020
She asked me to bring

00:25:12.260 --> 00:25:13.260
the last bowl to you.

00:25:13.740 --> 00:25:14.580
She also said

00:25:15.420 --> 00:25:17.660
thank you.

00:25:18.700 --> 00:25:20.260
What's your deal with her?

00:25:22.660 --> 00:25:23.620
What do you think?

00:25:24.660 --> 00:25:26.700
Sanyuan's got a story.

00:25:29.500 --> 00:25:31.060
I'm not sure about that,

00:25:31.300 --> 00:25:33.260
but I'm sure that it'll turn
into trouble

00:25:33.260 --> 00:25:34.706
if you keep eating liangpi like this.

00:25:36.510 --> 00:25:53.380
♪The stars and moon are dim;
the wind and dew are cold♪

00:25:59.420 --> 00:26:00.380
Yi Qin'e!

00:26:00.460 --> 00:26:01.580
What are you thinking?

00:26:01.820 --> 00:26:02.980
You're up.

00:26:03.720 --> 00:26:05.260
What's the point now?

00:26:05.260 --> 00:26:06.300
What were you doing?

00:26:06.300 --> 00:26:07.700
Focus a little.

00:26:08.740 --> 00:26:11.380
You and Gong Lili are
the same Li Hui Niang.

00:26:11.740 --> 00:26:13.140
When you hand off

00:26:13.140 --> 00:26:14.020
the role,

00:26:14.340 --> 00:26:16.020
it has to line up perfectly,

00:26:16.020 --> 00:26:17.340
or the director's idea

00:26:17.340 --> 00:26:18.540
will be completely pointless.

00:26:18.940 --> 00:26:19.780
Okay?

00:26:20.020 --> 00:26:21.340
Let's do it again.

00:26:22.140 --> 00:26:23.100
You step down first.

00:26:23.260 --> 00:26:24.460
Hurry, hurry.

00:26:24.700 --> 00:26:26.020
- Where to start?
- Wasting time.

00:26:26.220 --> 00:26:27.380
Let's start with the singing.

00:26:27.540 --> 00:26:28.580
Start with the singing.

00:26:29.380 --> 00:26:30.220
Ready, go.

00:26:34.910 --> 00:26:35.780
Sorry, hold on.

00:26:35.780 --> 00:26:37.060
Come here, do it like this.

00:26:37.620 --> 00:26:38.940
Yi Qin'e, you stay in the wing.

00:26:39.740 --> 00:26:41.140
The stars and moon are dim.

00:26:41.140 --> 00:26:41.980
You sing it.

00:26:43.340 --> 00:26:45.220
Gong Lili will lip-sync, okay?

00:26:45.250 --> 00:26:46.130
Why should I?

00:26:46.130 --> 00:26:47.380
We didn't agree on this.

00:26:47.380 --> 00:26:48.340
Listen to me. I know.

00:26:48.580 --> 00:26:49.620
Let's just try it, okay?

00:26:49.620 --> 00:26:50.860
Let's just give it a try.

00:26:50.860 --> 00:26:52.620
Come on, start with her singing.

00:26:52.620 --> 00:26:53.460
Ready.

00:26:54.180 --> 00:26:55.020
Go.

00:26:55.260 --> 00:27:11.540
♪The stars and moon are dim,
the wind and dew are cold♪

00:27:17.580 --> 00:27:20.940
How can that face sound so rustic?

00:27:21.060 --> 00:27:23.460
It's like after getting into bed,
with pants off,

00:27:23.900 --> 00:27:25.540
then someone passes gas.

00:27:26.300 --> 00:27:27.420
Just like that,

00:27:28.500 --> 00:27:29.540
the whole mood goes flat.

00:27:31.500 --> 00:27:32.340
Right.

00:27:35.620 --> 00:27:37.780
My wife gets all my wages.

00:27:41.780 --> 00:27:44.740
Check the amount, then sign here.

00:27:44.740 --> 00:27:46.020
(Payroll Disbursement Sheet)

00:27:46.020 --> 00:27:47.260
How much is my pay?

00:27:47.420 --> 00:27:48.420
Forty-five.

00:27:48.420 --> 00:27:49.820
It's written right here.

00:27:49.820 --> 00:27:51.220
What? Is something wrong?

00:27:51.460 --> 00:27:52.340
No, no.

00:27:53.380 --> 00:27:54.220
What do you mean?

00:27:54.400 --> 00:27:55.260
What's wrong?

00:27:55.260 --> 00:27:56.380
Why are you docking my pay?

00:27:59.500 --> 00:28:00.900
The Business Department ordered it.

00:28:00.900 --> 00:28:01.940
It's clearly written here.

00:28:01.940 --> 00:28:02.835
Go ask the department.

00:28:02.846 --> 00:28:03.620
They're all jerks.

00:28:04.780 --> 00:28:07.260
I make two yuan a show.

00:28:07.340 --> 00:28:09.060
And they deduct two yuan
for a wrong line!

00:28:10.700 --> 00:28:12.500
I work hard doing 7 or 8 shows a month.

00:28:12.500 --> 00:28:13.820
I'd earn more by not performing!

00:28:13.940 --> 00:28:15.100
Tell me. Is this fair?

00:28:15.960 --> 00:28:16.820
Is it fair?

00:28:16.820 --> 00:28:17.660
It makes no sense!

00:28:17.660 --> 00:28:18.900
Stop yelling here.

00:28:19.180 --> 00:28:21.060
Take it to the Business Department.

00:28:24.460 --> 00:28:25.860
See that? See?

00:28:25.980 --> 00:28:27.340
That is how the lead is treated.

00:28:27.820 --> 00:28:29.420
Fighting all day long.

00:28:29.420 --> 00:28:30.420
Fighting for what?

00:28:30.420 --> 00:28:31.940
- Lili.
- Move. Make way.

00:28:31.940 --> 00:28:32.940
- Don't be mad.
- Lili.

00:28:32.940 --> 00:28:34.380
- Jerks.
- Who upset you?

00:28:34.380 --> 00:28:35.540
I'll let them pay.

00:28:38.700 --> 00:28:39.540
Sign here.

00:28:40.300 --> 00:28:41.140
Come on.

00:28:42.020 --> 00:28:42.870
Exactly.

00:28:42.900 --> 00:28:43.740
What's wrong?

00:28:43.900 --> 00:28:44.740
It wasn't about you?

00:28:45.020 --> 00:28:45.940
Come on, line up.

00:28:46.780 --> 00:28:47.780
Line up, line up.

00:28:47.780 --> 00:28:49.500
Rule 5: Don't come to my office.

00:28:51.340 --> 00:28:52.740
That's Rule 7.

00:28:53.380 --> 00:28:54.780
I studied them carefully.

00:28:55.420 --> 00:28:56.346
Then, why are you here?

00:28:57.140 --> 00:28:57.976
You just got paid.

00:28:57.987 --> 00:28:59.020
You're carrying a fortune.

00:28:59.020 --> 00:29:00.340
I should at least take you back.

00:29:00.820 --> 00:29:01.660
Don't worry.

00:29:02.460 --> 00:29:03.340
I won't go in.

00:29:03.420 --> 00:29:05.380
Once you're inside, I'll leave.

00:29:05.780 --> 00:29:06.620
Who?

00:29:06.690 --> 00:29:07.530
What happened?

00:29:07.580 --> 00:29:08.420
What happened?

00:29:08.980 --> 00:29:10.540
They pulled out my valve core.

00:29:11.980 --> 00:29:13.660
What are you laughing at?

00:29:14.460 --> 00:29:15.300
One more rule.

00:29:15.300 --> 00:29:16.780
No pulling out others' valve cores.

00:29:17.380 --> 00:29:19.020
It's you out-of-towners.

00:29:20.300 --> 00:29:22.500
Where are your manners
at the provincial troupe?

00:29:27.100 --> 00:29:28.580
I used to think

00:29:28.780 --> 00:29:29.980
that on my own,

00:29:30.020 --> 00:29:32.020
I could help her find her footing.

00:29:32.900 --> 00:29:35.620
But now, I'm getting nervous too.

00:29:35.980 --> 00:29:36.900
Don't.

00:29:37.420 --> 00:29:39.420
We have to stand by some things,

00:29:40.020 --> 00:29:42.020
but we can adjust others a little.

00:29:42.180 --> 00:29:43.620
Take the vocal style, for example.

00:29:45.060 --> 00:29:46.220
Director Feng made one point

00:29:46.220 --> 00:29:47.700
that I think was right.

00:29:47.860 --> 00:29:49.140
Now, at the provincial troupe,

00:29:49.140 --> 00:29:50.780
it's all about blending in.

00:29:51.020 --> 00:29:52.420
In that process,

00:29:52.900 --> 00:29:54.700
the stronger one will stand firm.

00:29:57.140 --> 00:29:58.020
If I'm wrong,

00:29:58.020 --> 00:29:59.180
please don't take it to heart.

00:29:59.180 --> 00:30:00.020
You're not wrong.

00:30:00.380 --> 00:30:01.220
I was wrong.

00:30:02.300 --> 00:30:04.180
The kid was right last night too.

00:30:05.340 --> 00:30:06.820
After singing for so many years,

00:30:07.140 --> 00:30:09.900
I really don't know how to sing anymore.

00:30:11.540 --> 00:30:12.780
No matter how you sing,

00:30:13.220 --> 00:30:15.380
you have to get on stage first, right?

00:30:17.900 --> 00:30:18.740
That's right.

00:30:19.340 --> 00:30:20.460
You're absolutely right.

00:30:22.100 --> 00:30:22.940
Don't worry.

00:30:23.460 --> 00:30:24.980
If she can change her vocal style,

00:30:25.140 --> 00:30:27.460
I'll ask Director Feng
to yield the role.

00:30:27.860 --> 00:30:28.700
At the very least,

00:30:28.860 --> 00:30:31.220
Gui Yuan and Sha Sheng belong to Qin'e.

00:30:31.660 --> 00:30:32.500
Exactly.

00:30:50.700 --> 00:30:51.580
Stop worrying.

00:30:51.580 --> 00:30:52.493
I'm not having liangpi.

00:30:53.510 --> 00:30:54.380
Sit with me for a bit.

00:30:56.580 --> 00:30:57.900
I've got things on my mind.

00:30:58.740 --> 00:31:00.090
There's no one to talk to.

00:31:06.020 --> 00:31:07.820
Laidi is in trouble now.

00:31:11.900 --> 00:31:13.300
She's been here for a month

00:31:14.220 --> 00:31:15.220
and hasn't settled in.

00:31:16.180 --> 00:31:18.060
The vocal style Gou taught her

00:31:20.460 --> 00:31:23.460
doesn't fit the provincial troupe.

00:31:24.340 --> 00:31:26.820
The moment she sings,
it sounds like an out-of-towner.

00:31:27.180 --> 00:31:28.460
It's keeping her off the stage.

00:31:28.900 --> 00:31:29.780
One bowl of liangpi.

00:31:30.420 --> 00:31:31.260
Coming right up.

00:31:33.100 --> 00:31:34.180
Both vinegar and chili?

00:31:34.380 --> 00:31:35.220
Yes, please.

00:31:43.060 --> 00:31:44.300
- Here.
- Thanks.

00:31:51.860 --> 00:31:52.980
I want

00:31:53.660 --> 00:31:55.740
to find her a teacher

00:31:56.180 --> 00:31:57.700
to coach her vocal style.

00:31:58.340 --> 00:31:59.940
But that's not easy.

00:32:00.060 --> 00:32:01.100
It has to be a pro

00:32:01.100 --> 00:32:03.700
trained by the provincial troupe.

00:32:03.900 --> 00:32:06.140
But not someone currently with them.

00:32:06.180 --> 00:32:07.260
It's to avoid a conflict.

00:32:09.100 --> 00:32:09.940
Where can I

00:32:10.180 --> 00:32:11.380
find someone like that?

00:32:13.140 --> 00:32:14.180
Just keep looking.

00:32:14.940 --> 00:32:15.860
I really don't know.

00:32:16.700 --> 00:32:18.140
So, would you be willing?

00:32:19.460 --> 00:32:20.420
Coach her a bit.

00:32:20.580 --> 00:32:21.980
Ma'am, one bowl of liangpi.

00:32:22.340 --> 00:32:23.180
Coming right up.

00:32:24.060 --> 00:32:25.060
The Qinqiang opera

00:32:25.940 --> 00:32:27.180
has nothing to do with me.

00:32:47.380 --> 00:32:48.700
Why are you crying?

00:32:48.820 --> 00:32:49.660
Stop crying.

00:32:51.060 --> 00:32:52.820
You little rascal, testing me too?

00:32:53.060 --> 00:32:54.380
- Stop crying. Quiet.
- You...

00:32:54.500 --> 00:32:56.473
He's a baby. Why yell at him?

00:32:56.484 --> 00:32:57.808
- Give him to me.
- You hold him.

00:32:57.819 --> 00:32:58.580
You scared him.

00:33:01.220 --> 00:33:02.340
What did Lame Shan say?

00:33:02.420 --> 00:33:04.460
Give the baby a bottle first.
He's hungry.

00:33:04.820 --> 00:33:05.740
Okay, okay, don't cry.

00:33:06.620 --> 00:33:07.580
Let's let it go.

00:33:08.500 --> 00:33:10.100
- Let it go?
- It wasn't about you.

00:33:10.100 --> 00:33:11.460
- Okay, okay.
- I think you

00:33:11.460 --> 00:33:13.020
just can't protect your wife.

00:33:13.180 --> 00:33:14.340
Everyone's picking on me.

00:33:15.020 --> 00:33:16.420
How am I supposed to protect you?

00:33:16.860 --> 00:33:19.140
No one in the troupe
dares to mess with you.

00:33:20.060 --> 00:33:21.500
That new Yi Qin'e.

00:33:21.700 --> 00:33:22.700
That out-of-towner.

00:33:22.980 --> 00:33:24.700
She's my double in Gui Yuan
and Sha Sheng.

00:33:25.340 --> 00:33:26.660
Didn't Director Feng say so?

00:33:27.420 --> 00:33:28.620
She's just a double.

00:33:29.620 --> 00:33:30.900
Now that you've had the baby,

00:33:31.100 --> 00:33:32.260
your legs have gone stiff.

00:33:32.660 --> 00:33:33.980
You scream when you stretch.

00:33:33.980 --> 00:33:35.300
I hate seeing that.

00:33:35.820 --> 00:33:37.860
Her being your double is a good thing.

00:33:38.300 --> 00:33:39.340
Okay, okay. Right away.

00:33:39.340 --> 00:33:40.300
It sounds good for now.

00:33:40.420 --> 00:33:41.700
But things may change.

00:33:42.260 --> 00:33:43.100
What can she do?

00:33:43.500 --> 00:33:45.220
Her master, Gu,

00:33:45.300 --> 00:33:46.260
is a slippery one.

00:33:46.860 --> 00:33:48.540
Who knows what he's up to?

00:33:48.860 --> 00:33:50.740
That show-off old guy from out of town?

00:33:52.380 --> 00:33:53.300
Leave it to me.

00:33:54.660 --> 00:33:55.740
Don't go picking a fight.

00:33:55.860 --> 00:33:57.260
I still have the upper hand.

00:33:57.380 --> 00:33:58.460
If you do, I'll lose it.

00:33:59.300 --> 00:34:00.380
Did you hear me?

00:34:01.430 --> 00:34:02.760
I'm not some dummy.

00:34:03.820 --> 00:34:04.910
I have plenty of ways.

00:34:13.180 --> 00:34:14.020
Ms. Yuan.

00:34:14.820 --> 00:34:15.940
Chief sound guy.

00:34:16.660 --> 00:34:18.140
Long time no see.

00:34:18.420 --> 00:34:19.740
What brings you here?

00:34:20.540 --> 00:34:22.140
Lili is so scatterbrained.

00:34:22.140 --> 00:34:23.460
She lost her ID card.

00:34:23.500 --> 00:34:24.780
So, I'm getting my household card

00:34:25.020 --> 00:34:26.020
to apply for a new one.

00:34:26.020 --> 00:34:28.340
Wait. I'll find it after this stitch.

00:34:28.340 --> 00:34:29.260
Brioche stitch?

00:34:30.060 --> 00:34:31.140
You know about that?

00:34:31.220 --> 00:34:33.300
Lili knits too. It's all the rage now.

00:34:33.300 --> 00:34:35.060
Don't stop, or it'll puff up.

00:34:35.813 --> 00:34:36.900
I'll go look for it myself.

00:34:36.900 --> 00:34:37.806
It's in the second one.

00:34:37.817 --> 00:34:39.460
Second cabinet, personnel files.

00:34:39.820 --> 00:34:40.660
The second one.

00:34:40.780 --> 00:34:42.180
- Find it yourself.
- Don't stop.

00:34:47.300 --> 00:34:48.540
How's your husband been lately?

00:34:49.620 --> 00:34:50.780
Don't even mention him.

00:34:51.220 --> 00:34:53.300
Just thinking of him makes me mad.

00:34:54.570 --> 00:34:55.420
You know how he is.

00:34:55.420 --> 00:34:56.580
He often doesn't come home.

00:34:57.580 --> 00:34:59.260
When he does, he acts like a king.

00:35:00.260 --> 00:35:02.100
Socks on the floor, dirty clothes too.

00:35:02.100 --> 00:35:03.460
And he won't wash them himself.

00:35:04.540 --> 00:35:05.620
I have to do the laundry,

00:35:05.620 --> 00:35:07.740
watch the kid, and do chores.

00:35:07.740 --> 00:35:08.580
(Gu Cunxiao)

00:35:08.819 --> 00:35:10.499
And I still have to run
to the old folks.

00:35:10.740 --> 00:35:11.900
Every day he's with his buddy,

00:35:11.900 --> 00:35:13.740
drinking or playing mahjong.

00:35:13.740 --> 00:35:15.540
(Collective registration card)

00:35:18.900 --> 00:35:19.940
Hao Yigang, right?

00:35:19.940 --> 00:35:21.340
You're mailing a package, right?

00:35:21.340 --> 00:35:23.420
- Here, fill this out.
- Sure.

00:35:23.420 --> 00:35:25.180
Check the instructions at the bottom.

00:35:25.220 --> 00:35:26.460
For letters, write the address.

00:35:31.140 --> 00:35:32.660
Money transfer, please.

00:35:36.180 --> 00:35:38.300
Yi Maocai, Jiuyangou,
Hubeiliang, Ningzhou.

00:35:38.300 --> 00:35:39.140
Right?

00:35:41.700 --> 00:35:42.540
Is it right?

00:35:42.700 --> 00:35:44.380
Are the address and name right?

00:35:44.380 --> 00:35:45.500
Yeah, that's right.

00:35:45.620 --> 00:35:46.660
Why are you zoning out?

00:35:50.660 --> 00:35:51.500
Ma'am.

00:35:52.420 --> 00:35:53.900
Qin Xianglian and Bao Wenzheng

00:35:54.020 --> 00:35:56.260
sing San Dui Mian so well.

00:35:58.420 --> 00:35:59.260
Still,

00:35:59.420 --> 00:36:00.980
no matter how good the opera is,

00:36:01.220 --> 00:36:03.140
it can't beat your liangpi.

00:36:03.460 --> 00:36:04.300
Here.

00:36:04.500 --> 00:36:05.540
Come again if you like it.

00:36:07.860 --> 00:36:08.700
Here, have some.

00:36:09.260 --> 00:36:10.460
Nice, tasty liangpi.

00:36:10.460 --> 00:36:11.300
Sure.

00:36:11.780 --> 00:36:12.620
It's really good.

00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:13.860
One liangpi to go.

00:36:13.860 --> 00:36:15.300
Sure. Twenty-five cents.

00:36:15.660 --> 00:36:17.060
Both vinegar and chili?

00:36:18.660 --> 00:36:19.700
Ms. Hua.

00:36:20.230 --> 00:36:21.130
And you are?

00:36:21.140 --> 00:36:22.420
I'm Chu Jiahe.

00:36:23.020 --> 00:36:23.900
Chu Jiahe?

00:36:24.260 --> 00:36:25.100
It's me.

00:36:26.260 --> 00:36:27.660
Why are you selling liangpi?

00:36:30.460 --> 00:36:31.700
Why are you here too?

00:36:32.179 --> 00:36:33.492
You joined the provincial troupe?

00:36:35.460 --> 00:36:37.460
Then, you're colleagues with Laidi now.

00:36:37.460 --> 00:36:38.300
Well.

00:36:38.460 --> 00:36:39.980
She goes by Yi Qin'e now.

00:36:39.980 --> 00:36:42.060
She wants to make it big
in Qinqiang opera.

00:36:44.140 --> 00:36:46.260
I heard you're rehearsing You Xi Hu.

00:36:46.260 --> 00:36:47.500
Why aren't you rehearsing?

00:36:48.580 --> 00:36:49.420
Rehearsing?

00:36:50.780 --> 00:36:52.700
That has nothing to do with me anymore.

00:36:52.700 --> 00:36:54.380
I injured my lower back.

00:36:55.700 --> 00:36:56.620
What happened?

00:36:57.340 --> 00:36:58.220
Spondylolisthesis?

00:36:58.420 --> 00:36:59.820
Not that severe yet.

00:37:01.260 --> 00:37:02.380
You need to be careful.

00:37:02.380 --> 00:37:03.700
I have this problem too.

00:37:03.940 --> 00:37:05.220
I didn't treat it at first.

00:37:05.220 --> 00:37:07.220
And it just kept getting worse.

00:37:07.220 --> 00:37:08.220
Did you see the doctor?

00:37:08.220 --> 00:37:09.300
What did the doctor say?

00:37:09.460 --> 00:37:11.020
Didn't Yi Qin'e tell you?

00:37:11.460 --> 00:37:13.500
I was the B role.

00:37:13.500 --> 00:37:14.940
But the doctor said

00:37:15.180 --> 00:37:16.700
I need bed rest for three months.

00:37:17.060 --> 00:37:18.340
Then stay in bed.

00:37:18.340 --> 00:37:20.100
Why are you out wandering?

00:37:20.140 --> 00:37:21.860
You need to get treated.

00:37:22.260 --> 00:37:23.300
I'll take you somewhere.

00:37:23.300 --> 00:37:24.340
It'll definitely help.

00:37:25.180 --> 00:37:26.340
Laohei, watch the stall.

00:37:26.440 --> 00:37:27.300
Come on, let's go.

00:37:27.300 --> 00:37:28.580
Ms. Hua, no need.

00:37:28.580 --> 00:37:29.420
No way.

00:37:29.620 --> 00:37:31.900
I was going to buy you winter clothes.

00:37:32.180 --> 00:37:34.300
But I haven't shopped in Chang'an
since I got here.

00:37:34.660 --> 00:37:35.820
I might buy the wrong ones.

00:37:35.820 --> 00:37:36.740
Buy them yourself.

00:37:37.700 --> 00:37:38.740
Don't give me money.

00:37:38.980 --> 00:37:39.900
I have money.

00:37:40.140 --> 00:37:41.100
Take it.

00:37:41.140 --> 00:37:42.500
Things are pricey in Chang'an.

00:37:42.540 --> 00:37:43.500
Everything costs more.

00:37:43.980 --> 00:37:45.260
In that case,

00:37:45.380 --> 00:37:46.700
you should keep more for yourself.

00:37:46.700 --> 00:37:47.600
Keep it for yourself.

00:37:47.610 --> 00:37:49.620
I'm fine. I make 45 a month.

00:37:49.620 --> 00:37:51.220
I kept 15 for meals

00:37:51.300 --> 00:37:52.460
and sent 20 home.

00:37:52.460 --> 00:37:53.300
Keep it.

00:37:55.620 --> 00:37:58.820
Your family depended
on your money for years.

00:37:58.940 --> 00:38:00.540
If you'd taken my sister with you,

00:38:00.540 --> 00:38:02.220
she'd send money home too.

00:38:02.500 --> 00:38:03.340
All right.

00:38:05.980 --> 00:38:08.420
I'm old and not much use now.

00:38:09.500 --> 00:38:11.260
I'm worried
that if you hit trouble later,

00:38:11.740 --> 00:38:12.940
I won't be able to help much.

00:38:13.220 --> 00:38:14.260
Uncle, what's wrong?

00:38:14.380 --> 00:38:15.660
Nothing. I'm fine.

00:38:17.580 --> 00:38:19.020
Right, I'll take the money.

00:38:19.300 --> 00:38:20.140
Okay.

00:38:20.150 --> 00:38:21.020
Sir,

00:38:21.570 --> 00:38:23.160
- is Dr. Hu here?
- Yes.

00:38:23.270 --> 00:38:25.300
Sanyuan, Ms. Hua is here.

00:38:25.340 --> 00:38:26.340
Sit here for now.

00:38:28.820 --> 00:38:29.660
What brings you here?

00:38:30.700 --> 00:38:31.486
She needs treatment

00:38:31.497 --> 00:38:32.862
for her injured back, just like me.

00:38:32.873 --> 00:38:33.820
Give her a massage.

00:38:34.310 --> 00:38:36.049
Isn't this the girl
from our trainee class?

00:38:39.380 --> 00:38:41.060
You can't get up that fast.

00:38:41.060 --> 00:38:41.980
You'll twist it again.

00:38:41.980 --> 00:38:42.980
You need to treat it.

00:38:42.980 --> 00:38:44.060
I don't need your pity.

00:38:47.300 --> 00:38:48.140
I'll go talk to her.

00:38:53.090 --> 00:38:54.110
Aunt Hua.

00:38:56.820 --> 00:38:57.700
Laidi,

00:38:59.180 --> 00:39:00.660
you've grown up so much.

00:39:36.780 --> 00:39:37.620
Chu Jiahe.

00:39:38.510 --> 00:39:39.500
Are you okay?

00:39:39.900 --> 00:39:40.740
Go away.

00:39:45.780 --> 00:39:47.740
I don't care about your grudge
with Qin'e.

00:39:48.300 --> 00:39:50.620
As a senior in Qinqiang opera,

00:39:51.180 --> 00:39:52.620
I have to tell you this.

00:39:53.060 --> 00:39:54.740
You must treat this illness ASAP.

00:39:55.220 --> 00:39:56.260
If you don't treat it,

00:39:56.540 --> 00:39:58.260
you might never take the stage again.

00:39:59.420 --> 00:40:01.300
Don't treat me like Qin'e's uncle.

00:40:01.780 --> 00:40:03.580
Just see me as a local from Ningzhou.

00:40:04.860 --> 00:40:06.260
Trust me just this once.

00:40:06.346 --> 00:40:07.740
Even if you don't let me treat you,

00:40:07.740 --> 00:40:09.260
you must go to a hospital.

00:40:10.660 --> 00:40:12.820
If you don't cure it, you'll be ruined.

00:40:14.540 --> 00:40:15.580
Do you hear me?

00:40:18.180 --> 00:40:19.060
You have to treat it.

00:40:47.220 --> 00:40:48.980
I've heard about you for a long time.

00:40:49.940 --> 00:40:52.860
Ningzhou County Troupe's
lead Qingyi role.

00:40:52.860 --> 00:40:54.660
Such a great beauty.

00:40:55.300 --> 00:40:57.140
It's be a pity that you quit singing.

00:40:57.580 --> 00:40:59.260
Nothing to pity.

00:40:59.870 --> 00:41:00.740
Come on, Master Gu.

00:41:00.740 --> 00:41:01.580
Such a pity.

00:41:01.620 --> 00:41:02.460
A toast to you.

00:41:02.660 --> 00:41:03.780
Alright, alright.

00:41:05.060 --> 00:41:06.420
You're from our troupe.

00:41:06.420 --> 00:41:07.780
That makes us family.

00:41:08.140 --> 00:41:08.980
Bottoms up.

00:41:09.700 --> 00:41:10.540
Sure.

00:41:15.100 --> 00:41:15.940
Eat up, eat up.

00:41:17.340 --> 00:41:18.180
Just enjoy your food.

00:41:21.540 --> 00:41:22.700
Let me fill your glass.

00:41:23.500 --> 00:41:25.220
I have to toast you again.

00:41:25.540 --> 00:41:26.780
To you, Master Gou,

00:41:26.940 --> 00:41:28.340
and the other two masters.

00:41:28.650 --> 00:41:30.740
You guys trained the kid.

00:41:31.860 --> 00:41:32.780
If you put it that way,

00:41:32.780 --> 00:41:34.780
I should be toasting you.

00:41:34.900 --> 00:41:36.740
You saw the kid's potential first.

00:41:37.300 --> 00:41:39.740
You're the kid's true mentor.

00:41:39.780 --> 00:41:40.940
Not at all!

00:41:41.060 --> 00:41:42.700
The kid will rely on you from now on.

00:41:42.820 --> 00:41:43.740
Don't worry about that!

00:41:44.580 --> 00:41:46.980
I'd work my old bones to dust

00:41:47.180 --> 00:41:48.140
to make sure our kid

00:41:48.460 --> 00:41:51.220
shines on the big stage of Chang'an!

00:41:51.340 --> 00:41:52.660
Good, good! Come on!

00:41:52.660 --> 00:41:53.740
- Come on!
- Cheers to you!

00:41:53.740 --> 00:41:54.980
Join us, Qin'e! Hurry!

00:41:55.580 --> 00:41:56.420
Cheers!

00:41:59.020 --> 00:42:00.460
I never felt it before,

00:42:00.820 --> 00:42:03.780
but seeing Qin'e and Jiahe today

00:42:04.260 --> 00:42:05.940
makes me truly feel I'm getting old.

00:42:06.100 --> 00:42:08.020
What are you saying? You're not old!

00:42:08.020 --> 00:42:09.180
You're so young!

00:42:09.540 --> 00:42:10.380
Let me tell you.

00:42:10.580 --> 00:42:12.740
You are of great use right now!

00:42:13.260 --> 00:42:15.620
As for our kid's singing and diction,

00:42:15.940 --> 00:42:17.700
- she needs to...
- Stop talking!

00:42:18.060 --> 00:42:18.900
Eat up, eat up!

00:42:19.020 --> 00:42:20.180
We're drinking fast.

00:42:20.340 --> 00:42:21.380
You should sit down too.

00:42:21.620 --> 00:42:23.020
One more dish. Almost done.

00:42:26.300 --> 00:42:27.580
Are you okay here?

00:42:28.980 --> 00:42:30.540
Tell me what you want to eat.

00:42:30.740 --> 00:42:31.700
I'll cook for you.

00:42:43.660 --> 00:42:45.500
Here's a ready-made vocal style teacher.

00:42:45.980 --> 00:42:47.460
She was once coached by the teacher

00:42:47.540 --> 00:42:49.020
from the provincial troupe.

00:42:50.420 --> 00:42:52.740
Why didn't you let me say it?

00:42:55.300 --> 00:42:56.460
I'll bring it up later.

00:42:56.460 --> 00:42:57.380
Go back in and drink.

00:42:57.380 --> 00:42:58.300
Drink up.

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:06.940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

00:43:09.640 --> 00:43:10.510
Laidi.

00:43:10.590 --> 00:43:11.510
Wake up.

00:43:11.630 --> 00:43:12.500
Come with me.

00:43:12.550 --> 00:43:16.480
Hu Sanyuan.

00:43:18.590 --> 00:43:19.960
Go play the drums for a living.

00:43:20.070 --> 00:43:22.190
My drum's only worth
fifty cents of this.

00:43:22.190 --> 00:43:24.070
The rest is your duet with Qin'e.

00:43:24.070 --> 00:43:26.000
Gu Cunxiao of the provincial troupe

00:43:26.000 --> 00:43:27.070
is a total creep!

00:43:27.070 --> 00:43:28.320
I demand an explanation today.

00:43:29.800 --> 00:43:30.760
What's going on?

00:43:30.880 --> 00:43:31.730
Where are you from?

00:43:31.800 --> 00:43:32.660
Take your time.

00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:41.620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:43:43.090 --> 00:43:47.930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:43:49.370 --> 00:43:53.560
♪We met and brushed past♪

00:43:55.120 --> 00:44:02.420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:20.540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

00:44:22.140 --> 00:44:27.710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

00:44:28.830 --> 00:44:32.890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:39.610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

00:44:40.770 --> 00:44:44.970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:51.640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

00:44:52.810 --> 00:44:57.500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

00:44:58.180 --> 00:45:03.350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

00:45:04.020 --> 00:45:09.050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:15.510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:45:15.890 --> 00:45:21.170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

00:45:22.120 --> 00:45:27.930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

00:45:27.930 --> 00:45:33.350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:39.410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:44.920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

00:45:45.940 --> 00:45:51.220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

00:45:52.020 --> 00:46:01.050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪